Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Toss on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on middle rack until lightly browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes} total. (You'll add more to the sheet after 10 minutes.)

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels; season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of cooking oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{6-8%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in Step 4).

While chicken cooks, trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and minced).

Once potatoes have roasted ~{10%minutes}, remove baking sheet from oven; carefully toss, keeping on one side.

Toss green beans on empty side with a drizzle of cooking oil and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Return to middle rack until veggies are tender, ~{10-12%minutes} more.

Once chicken is browned all over, transfer to a second baking sheet.

Roast on top rack until chicken is cooked through, ~{8-12%minutes}. Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

Heat a drizzle of cooking oil in pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add garlic and @dried thyme{1%teaspoon}; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{2}, @honey{2%teaspoon}, and 1⁄4 cup water (1⁄2 cup for 4 servings). Simmer, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan, until reduced by half, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If sauce seems too thick, stir in a splash or two of water.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken, green beans, and potatoes between plates. Drizzle chicken with sauce and serve.

Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.